#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:287
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Keeping the `cvf` (`tvf` or `xvf`) keys unchanged for all backup operations and simply adding the compression key to the end of the keys makes the command easier to understand (e.g., `cvfz` or `cvfj`, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a compressed backup with `bzip`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:291
msgid "Creating a compressed backup with `bzip` is done with the keys `cvfj`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar cvfj backup.tar.bz2 dirname/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:299
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                       |\n"
"|-----|-----------------------------------|\n"
"| `j` |\tCompresses the backup in _bzip2_. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The `.tbz` and `.tb2` extensions are equivalent to `.tar.bz2` extensions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:304
#, no-wrap
msgid "Compression `compress`, `gzip`, `bzip2`, `lzip` and `xz`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:307
msgid ""
"Compression, and consequently decompression, will have an impact on resource "
"consumption (time and CPU usage)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:309
msgid ""
"Here is a ranking of the compression of a set of text files, from least to "
"most efficient:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:315
msgid ""
"- compress (`.tar.Z`)  - gzip (`.tar.gz`)  - bzip2 (`.tar.bz2`)  - lzip (`."
"tar.lz`)  - xz (`.tar.xz`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:316
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add a file or directory to an existing backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:319
msgid "It is possible to add one or more items to an existing backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:320
#, no-wrap
msgid "tar {r|A}[key(s)] [device] [file(s)]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:325
msgid "To add `/etc/passwd` to the backup `/backups/home.133.tar`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:326
#, no-wrap
msgid "[root]# tar rvf /backups/home.133.tar /etc/passwd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:331
msgid ""
"Adding a directory is similar. Here add `dirtoadd` to `backup_name.tar`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:332
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar rvf backup_name.tar dirtoadd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:340
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                                                                      |\n"
"|-----|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `r` |\tAdds one or more files at the end of a direct access media backup (hard disk).   |\n"
"| `A` |\tAdds one or more files at the end of a backup on sequential access media (tape). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "    It is not possible to add files or folders to a compressed backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:350
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ tar rvfz backup.tgz filetoadd\n"
"    tar: Cannot update compressed archives\n"
"    Try `tar --help' or `tar --usage' for more information.\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If the backup was performed in relative mode, add files in relative mode. If the backup was done in absolute mode, add files in absolute mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:356
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Mixing modes can cause problems when restoring.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "List the contents of a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:360
msgid "Viewing the contents of a backup without extracting it is possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:361
#, no-wrap
msgid "tar t[key(s)] [device]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key |\tDescription                                           |\n"
"|-----|-------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `t` |\tDisplays the content of a backup (compressed or not). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:370
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:720
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ tar tvf backup.tar\n"
"$ tar tvfz backup.tar.gz\n"
"$ tar tvfj backup.tar.bz2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:378
msgid ""
"When the number of files in a backup becomes large, it is possible to _pipe_ "
"the result of the `tar` command to a _pager_ (`more`, `less`, `most`, etc.):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar tvf backup.tar | less\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:386
#, no-wrap
msgid "    To list or retrieve the contents of a backup, it is not necessary to mention the compression algorithm used when the backup was created. That is, a `tar tvf` is equivalent to `tar tvfj`, to read the contents, and a `tar xvf` is equivalent to `tar xvfj`, to extract.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Always check the contents of a backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:391
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check the integrity of a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:394
msgid ""
"The integrity of a backup can be tested with the `W` key at the time of its "
"creation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:395
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar cvfW file_name.tar dir/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:400
msgid ""
"The integrity of a backup can be tested with the key `d` after its creation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:401
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar vfd file_name.tar dir/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:408
#, no-wrap
msgid "    By adding a second `v` to the previous key, you will get the list of archived files as well as the differences between the archived files and those present in the file system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:419
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ tar vvfd  /tmp/quodlibet.tar .quodlibet/\n"
"    drwxr-x--- rockstar/rockstar     0 2021-05-21 00:11 .quodlibet/\n"
"    -rw-r--r-- rockstar/rockstar     0 2021-05-19 00:59 .quodlibet/queue\n"
"    [â¦]\n"
"    -rw------- rockstar/rockstar  3323 2021-05-21 00:11 .quodlibet/config\n"
"    .quodlibet/config: Mod time differs\n"
"    .quodlibet/config: Size differs\n"
"    [â¦]\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:421
msgid ""
"The `W` key is also used to compare the content of an archive against the "
"filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ tar tvfW file_name.tar\n"
"Verify 1/file1\n"
"1/file1: Mod time differs\n"
"1/file1: Size differs\n"
"Verify 1/file2\n"
"Verify 1/file3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:432
msgid ""
"The verification with the `W` key cannot be done with a compressed archive. "
"The key `d` must be used:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:433
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ tar dfz file_name.tgz\n"
"$ tar dfj file_name.tar.bz2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:438
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extract (_untar_) a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:441
msgid "Extract (_untar_) a ``*.tar`` backup is done with the `xvf` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:443
msgid ""
"Extract the `etc/exports` file from the `/savings/etc.133.tar` backup into "
"the `etc` directory of the active directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:444
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ tar xvf /backups/etc.133.tar etc/exports\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:449
msgid ""
"Extract all files from the compressed backup `/backups/home.133.tar.bz2` "
"into the active directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:450
#, no-wrap
msgid "[root]# tar xvfj /backups/home.133.tar.bz2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:455
msgid ""
"Extract all files from the backup `/backups/etc.133.P.tar` to their original "
"directory:"
